documents.content: Indian Cricketers – Career Statistics Sachin Tendulkar Role: Batsman Matches 664 Runs 34,357 Average 48.52 Centuries 100 Virat Kohli Role: Batsman Matches 500+ Runs 26,000+ Average 57+ Centuries 80+ MS Dhoni Role: Wicketkeeper-Batsman Matches 538 Runs 17,000+ Average 45+ Catches/Stumpings 634/195 Kapil Dev Role: All-rounder Matches 356 Runs 9,000+ Wickets 687 Average 29.64

Indian Cricketers – Records and Milestones Sachin Tendulkar  Most runs in international cricket  First to score 200 in ODIs Virat Kohli  Fastest to 8,000, 9,000, 10,000 ODI runs MS Dhoni  Most matches as captain for India  Only captain to win all ICC trophies Kapil Dev  Only player with 5,000+ runs and 400+ wickets in Tests

Indian Cricketers – Family and Early Life Sachin Tendulkar Born in Mumbai, Maharashtra. Married to Anjali Tendulkar; two children, Sara and Arjun. Virat Kohli Born in Delhi. Married to actress Anushka Sharma; one daughter, Vamika. MS Dhoni Born in Ranchi, Jharkhand. Married to Sakshi Singh Dhoni; one daughter, Ziva. Kapil Dev Born in Chandigarh. Married to Romi Bhatia; one daughter, Amiya Dev.

Indian Cricketers – Achievements and Awards Sachin Tendulkar  Most international centuries (100)  Bharat Ratna awardee  2011 World Cup winner Virat Kohli  ICC Cricketer of the Decade  Led India to Test series win in Australia MS Dhoni  Led India to 2007 T20 and 2011 ODI World Cup wins  Padma Bhushan recipient Kapil Dev  1983 World Cup-winning captain  Named Indian Cricketer of the Century (2002)
